## 📝 2. Neovim Core Setup (LazyVim structure)
Your configuration automatically builds the core system packages (git, gcc, ripgrep, LSPs) that LazyVim needs to operate at peak speed. To initialize it, you need to map out your initial configuration profile.

* The Target Location: ~/.config/nvim/
* The Action: Run the automated clone command to instantiate the boilerplate framework layout:

git clone https://github.com ~/.config/nvim

* The Files: This will cleanly lay out the structure you mentioned:
* ~/.config/nvim/init.lua: The orchestrator file that loads the core Neovim parameters and sets up the plugin managers.
   * ~/.config/nvim/lua/config/keymaps.lua: The specific script file where you will write out your custom keyboard overrides and shortcuts.

