## 📸 3. Niri Workspace Shortcuts (Screenshots)
Your system configuration installs grim, slurp, and swappy, but Niri needs to know exactly which physical keys trigger them.

* The Location: ~/.config/niri/config.kdl
* The Step: Open or generate your Niri configuration and bind your physical PrintScreen key to launch the interactive canvas capture module by adding this inside the binds { ... } block:

binds {
    Mod+Print { spawn "sh" "-c" "grim -g \"$(slurp)\" - | swappy -f -"; }
}


