## 🔒 4. Secure Boot Enforcement (Lanzaboote)
You cannot initialize motherboard security parameters on your very first system installation phase. You must establish a standard boot generation sequence first, then switch to the security module.

* Step A: Reboot into your computer's BIOS screen and set your Secure Boot keys parameter to "Setup Mode" or "Erase custom keys".
* Step B: Boot into NixOS and update /etc/nixos/configuration.nix by swapping the legacy boot.loader.systemd-boot values for Lanzaboote:

boot.loader.systemd-boot.enable = pkgs.lib.mkForce false;
boot.loader.efi.canTouchEfiVariables = true;
boot.lanzaboote = {
  enable = true;
  pkiBundle = "/etc/secureboot";
};

* Step C: Execute the cryptographic key creation script pipelines in your terminal terminal:

sudo sbctl create-keys
sudo nixos-rebuild switch
sudo sbctl enroll-keys --microsoft

* Step D: Reboot your machine one final time, go back into your BIOS, and toggle Secure Boot back to "Enabled".

